go 2015 (or just missed <a class="readmore btn" href="http://wordpress.melissacabral.com/wordcamp-san-diego-2015-speaker-slide-round-up/">Read More</a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"Melissa";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3220:"<p><a title="Pippin Williamson speaking at WCSD15 by Rob Bertholf, on Flickr" href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/robbertholf/16337280513"><img src="https://farm9.staticflickr.com/8742/16337280513_97023cf44e_z.jpg" alt="Pippin Williamson speaking at WCSD15" width="640" height="424" /></a><br />\nIf you couldn&#8217;t make it to WordCamp San Diego 2015 (or just missed a session you wanted to attend), here&#8217;s a round-up of all the speaker slides I could find. I&#8217;ll add more as they turn up!</p>\n<h2>Saturday</h2>\n<h3>Admin Track</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Hristo Pandjarov &#8211; <a href="http://www.slideshare.net/pandjarov/hristo-pandjarov-wordcamp-san-diego-why-is-my-website-slow?qid=ff8e9092-8457-47d8-84c1-8a2d79e53394&amp;v=qf1&amp;b=&amp;from_search=1">Why is my Website Slow?</a></li>\n<li>Jason Cosper &#8211; <a href="http://jasoncosper.com/talks/wcsd/2015/#0">OMG WTF <strong>SSL</strong>?</a></li>\n<li>Chris Wiegman &#8211; <a href="https://speakerdeck.com/chriswiegman/vetting-a-plugin-wordcamp-san-diego-2015">Vetting a Plugin</a></li>\n<li>Michele Butcher &#8211; <a href="http://www.slideshare.net/michelebutcher/your-site-has-been-hacked-now-what?qid=abe27ffe-c36e-46cb-b097-8e618819f618&amp;v=default&amp;b=&amp;from_search=2">Your site has been hacked &#8211; now what?</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Beginner Track</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Matt Cromwell &#8211; <a href="http://slides.mattcromwell.com/presentation/wordcamp-san-diego-2015/#1">Properly setting up your site</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Design Track</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Chris Ford &#8211; <a href="https://speakerdeck.com/ci_chrisford/wcsd-2015-think-outside-the-stock">Think Outside the Stock</a></li>\n<li>Natalie MacLees &#8211; <a href="http://nataliemac.github.io/wcsd2015/#/">Responsive Design</a></li>\n<li>David Sutoyo &#8211; <a href="https://speakerdeck.com/dsutoyo/shaping-your-themes-with-style">Shaping your Themes with Style</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Developer Track</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Tomas Puig &#8211; <a href="http://www.slideshare.net/photoflame42/wordpress-as-the-content-management-system-of-record?qid=ff8e9092-8457-47d8-84c1-8a2d79e53394&amp;v=qf1&amp;b=&amp;from_search=5">The Future of WordPress</a></li>\n<li>Roy Sivan &#8211; <a href="http://www.slideshare.net/royssivan/wordcamp-san-diego-2015-wordpress-wpapi-and-web-applications?qid=761bab97-9819-414b-b852-a149b7976a52&amp;v=qf1&amp;b=&amp;from_search=1">The WordPress REST API for Web Apps</a></li>\n<li>Dave Jesch &#8211; <a href="https://speakerdeck.com/spectromtech/dave-jesch-wordcamp-san-diego-2015-object-oriented-programming-and-wordpress">OOP Made Easy</a> &#8211; Oject Oriented Programming + WordPress</li>\n<li>Marty Thornley &#8211; <a href="http://www.slideshare.net/MartyThornley/integrating-external-apis-with-wordpress">Integrating External APIs</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Sunday!</h2>\n<h3>Product Business Track</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Andrew Norcross &#8211; <a href="https://speakerdeck.com/norcross/sizing-a-market">Sizing a Market</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Service Business Track</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Rebecca Gill &#8211; <a href="http://www.slideshare.net/rebeccagill/wcsd-expectations-management-v3?qid=5acaa7a8-a1df-47e4-a985-d653f42e6aa9&amp;v=qf1&amp;b=&amp;from_search=1">Expectations Management</a></li>\n</ul>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:87:"http://wo